## Rationale

- Aligns with intended battery-first system behavior
- Avoids conflicting power domains (USB vs battery vs LDO)
- Preserves full USB functionality
- Enables internal DC/DC for improved efficiency
- Simplifies power tree and reduces unnecessary losses

---

## Tradeoffs

### Advantages
- Cleaner architecture
- Better battery efficiency
- Fewer components (LDO removed)
- Consistent system behavior across power modes

### Considerations
- Must ensure system rail remains within VDDH operating range
- Low-voltage cutoff must prevent operation below VDDH minimum
- Requires careful routing of USB VBUS separately from system rail

---

## Notes

This change resolves a structural mismatch between:
- system intent (battery-powered device)
- and initial configuration (USB-powered reference)

This is a critical architectural correction and will impact:
- schematic organization
- power routing
- bring-up procedure

Future work:
- verify VDDH operating range vs charger output behavior
- confirm USB VBUS detection wiring
- finalize decoupling and DC/DC component placement